	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				As has been pointed out, 2 of these do make Silk Thread and 2 Silk Threads make Silk Bandages if succesful.  As to the reason you would want them over regular bandages, the reason is simple.  Look at the weight.  Silk Bandages weight .2 as opposed to regular bandagesthat are .5 so it doesn't take a genius to figure out that you can carry 25 Silk bandages for the same weight that would make up 10 regular bandages.  Certainly a big deal if you have low STR or are looking for a way to offset the weight of heavy armor:-)  Making these became trivial at about skill level 15-20.  Same with the Silk Swatches made from Spider Silk (not spiderling).<BR>
<BR>
Kharlkuhlinayn<BR>
Steel Warrior of the 15th Season<BR>
Morell-Thule
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
